content:
A dataset’s extended metadata (XMD) file allows you to customize the formatting of dashboards associated with the dataset. You can update the XMD file through the dataset’s edit page.

Available in Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience, available with CRM Analytics for an extra cost in Enterprise, Performance, and Unlimited Editions, also available in Developer Edition.

An XMD file must use XMD 2.0 syntax and be no greater than 5 MB. Refer to Extended Metadata (XMD) Developer Guide for information about extended metadata files and XMD 2.0 syntax.

To update the XMD file:

*   On the CRM Analytics page, click the Datasets tab.
*   Hover over the dataset that you want to update, click , and then click Edit.
*   Under Extended Metadata File, click , and then select Download as a backup.
*   Under Extended Metadata File, click , and then select Replace with your new XMD file.

If the XMD file is not valid, you will see an error message. Correct the syntax of the file and upload it again.

Refer to Extended Metadata (XMD) Developer Guide for information about converting extended metadata files to XMD 2.0 syntax.
title: Customizing Dataset Formatting with Extended Metadata
